# Migrations Directory

This directory contains database migration files.

## Naming Convention
Migrations are named: `YYYYMMDDHHMMSS_description.sql`

Example: `20240206120000_add_customer_notes.sql`

## Creating Migrations
Use the migrate tool:
```bash
python migrate.py --create "add customer notes"
```

## Migration Format
Each migration should include:
- Forward migration SQL (inside BEGIN/COMMIT)
- Rollback SQL as comments (prefixed with `-- ROLLBACK:`)

Example:
```sql
BEGIN;

-- Add new column
ALTER TABLE customers ADD COLUMN notes TEXT;

-- ROLLBACK: ALTER TABLE customers DROP COLUMN notes;

COMMIT;
```
